Four people have been killed and seventeen others injured when a taxi and light motor vehicle collided on the R34 near Newcastle in KwaZulu-Natal.ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene and found both wrecked vehicles in the middle of the road. Several patients were found lying around the two vehicles.&#8220;Upon inspection, paramedics found the lifeless bodies of four lying on the scene.&#8220;Paramedics assessed the patients and found that all four had already succumbed to their injuries. Unfortunately, nothing could be done for the patients and they were declared dead by another service,&#8221; ER24 said in a statement.Seventeen other patients were found on the scene, assessments showed that the injuries sustained ranged from minor to moderate.Paramedics treated the patients and thereafter after transported them to various hospitals in the area for urgent treatment.The details surrounding the incident are not yet known but local authorities were on scene for further investigations.TNA Reporter